# id: AbstractJsonHttpMessageConverter -> public void setPrefixJson(boolean prefixJson)
commentText:
Indicate whether the JSON output by this view should be prefixed with ")]}', "._Default is {@code false}._

Prefixing the JSON string in this manner is used to help prevent JSON_Hijacking. The prefix renders the string syntactically invalid as a script_so that it cannot be hijacked._This prefix should be stripped before parsing the string as JSON._@see #setJsonPrefix
codeText: public void setPrefixJson(boolean prefixJson) {_		this.jsonPrefix = (prefixJson ? ")]}', " : null)__	}
